HEADWORD: Mysteriousness
<hw>Mys*te"ri*ous*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or
quality of being mysterious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something mysterious; a mystery.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mysterize</ent>⟦br⟧
